dc_title_s: Map of the Territory of Minnesota exhibiting the route of the expedition ot the Red River of the north, in the summer of 1849
dc_description_s: 1 map ; 61 x 70 cm|Relief shown by hachures and spot heights.|Shows Minnesota and parts of Wisconsin, Iowa, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota, Manitoba, and Ontario.|Gives both Indian and later place names.|Shows "Proposed line of grants for railroads."
